                {
                    "id": "edeeb7d8262449ce952f7",
                    "stepText": "Finally, using the horizontal component from Step 5 ($!$7.5\\,m/s$!$) and an estimated vertical component of about $!$9.2\\,m/s$!$ (obtained by applying the correct vertical formula to find the velocity at a displacement of $!$4.3\\,m$!$), calculate the magnitude of the water balloon's velocity at half its maximum height. (Round your answer to one decimal place.)",
