        {
            "id": "df68e805500541dfa933b",
            "questionText": "A delivery drone starts from rest at a warehouse. It ascends vertically with a constant acceleration of $!$a_1 = 2\\, m/s^2$!$ for a duration of $!$t_1 = 10\\,s$!$. Then, it flies horizontally at a constant velocity for $!$t_2 = 30\\,s$!$ to deliver a package. After dropping the package, the drone decelerates horizontally at a constant rate of $!$a_2 = -1\\, m/s^2$!$ for a duration of $!$t_3 = 15\\,s$!$ before landing. Calculate the total displacement (magnitude) of the drone from its starting point at the warehouse.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "f0156b73208e4f49927ad",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the appropriate kinematics formula to calculate the vertical displacement for an object starting from rest under constant acceleration. Which formula should you use?",
